        "faq_yqgwMK": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "margin_top": 32,
            "margin_bottom": 32,
            "gap": 0,
            "faq_content": "<title>Is OmniShell fully waterproof?</title>\n<p>Yes. OmniShell is built with a 3-layer laminated fabric featuring a Dermizax™ membrane, delivering 20K waterproof protection. Combined with fully seam-sealed construction, it prevents water from entering through both the fabric and stitched seams, keeping you dry in heavy rain and snowy conditions.</p>\n<title>Will it feel hot during active use?</title>\n<p>Not at all. OmniShell combines 10K breathability with the moisture-permeable Dermizax™ membrane, allowing excess heat and perspiration to escape while keeping rain out. It's designed for hiking, skiing, climbing, and other high-output activities where comfort matters.</p>\n<title>What weather is OmniShell designed for?</title>\n<p>OmniShell is built for unpredictable conditions—from rainy city commutes to alpine adventures. It performs well in rain, wind, and snow, and works as a versatile outer shell that can be layered over insulating garments in colder temperatures.\n</p><title>What is the difference between waterproof fabric and the DWR finish?</title>\n<p>The Dermizax™ membrane provides the jacket's waterproof barrier, preventing water from penetrating the fabric. The PFAS-free DWR finish helps rain bead up and roll off the outer surface, reducing moisture buildup while using a more environmentally responsible water-repellent treatment.\n</p><title>How should I care for OmniShell?</title>\n<p>Wash the jacket according to the care label using a technical outerwear detergent when possible. Avoid fabric softeners and bleach, as they can reduce performance. Tumble dry on low heat or follow the care instructions to help restore the DWR finish when needed. Proper care will help maintain both waterproof performance and breathability.</p>",
            "target_tab": "faq"
          }
        },
